<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="596" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/1228</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Mexican Affairs,
                                Department of State</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-11"><hi rend="italic">July 11,
                                1922</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Mr. Branch appeared to be
                            satisfied with his Conference with you this morning, and intimated that
                            he thought the Committee would give Mr. de la Huerta a negative answer
                            to his request for a loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">atthew</hi>] E. H[<hi rend="smallcaps">anna</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>